upsert_activity_by_source:

Input
provider: str – source system (e.g., "strava")
external_id: str – unique ID from provider
activity_data: dict – activity fields (name, duration, distance, etc.)

Output
Activity object (created or updated)

function upsert_activity_by_source(provider, external_id, activity_data):

    validate provider is not empty
    validate external_id is not empty
    validate activity_data is not null

    existing = find_activity_by_provider_and_external_id(provider, external_id)

    if existing exists:
        update existing activity with activity_data
        save updated activity
        return updated activity
    else:
        new_activity = create activity with provider, external_id, activity_data
        save new_activity
        return new_activity

Validation Rules
provider must not be empty
external_id must not be empty
activity_data must contain required fields (e.g., name, timestamp)
Prevent duplicate (provider, external_id) pairs

delete_activity:

Input
activity_id: str

Output
boolean (true if deleted, false if not found)

function delete_activity(activity_id):

    validate activity_id is not empty

    activity = find activity by id

    if activity does not exist:
        return false

    delete activity from database

    return true

Validation Rules
activity_id must not be empty

